<br>
Level is God<br>
AC is King (resists against AE mobs)<br>
Stats are queen<br>
<br>
In otherwords while AC is in fact the overall most important factor in armor it is not the ONLY thing.  there is a balance to be had and neglecting stats will see a decrease in perfermance.<br>
<br>
As far as stats of importance to fighter types this is what has been gleaned.<br>
<br>
STR is important to increase damage marginally and increase carry weight overall good to have some but not the stat that should be focused on too heavily.<br>
<br>
STA is the king of melee stats.  Added HP and the reduction/elimination of being stunned from normal frontal attacks by many average mobs i.e. not bosses (the second point is debated but I have seen a large decrease in stuns<br>
<br>
AGL if below 75 then 5 points are needed to &quot;fix&quot; the deficit.  The difference in AC made from 70 to 75 is often 40 to 60AC by the time you reach 50s.  Also further increases do increase AC but by such negligble amounts as to not be over concerning.<br>
<br>
DEX is important to paladins since we get self procs and several of our holy swords make use of procs.  Also Dex helps in channelling spells.  A necro friend decked out in good dex gear is often quite able to still get barrages of spells off even with multiple dungeon creatures beating on him.<br>
<br>
WIS is important cause we have some very nice spells which are VERY expensive to cast.  The healing wave spells are major mana hogs but are of such use on AE raids that they can literally turn a battle around.  Also we get many clerical buffs which due to hybrid penalty cost us 1.5 times the normal amount clerics pay.  And considering clerics complain about mana usage on buffs think of where that leaves us.<br>
<br>
INT not so important to us but it does aid in the learning of skills.  If your working on a craft skill or even a weapon skill higher int has been linked to faster learning.<br>
<br>
CHA Again not such a big deal for us except to make some extra money and get better deals off vendors.  However as Act of Valor is picked up as an AA skill I would like to see how CHA affects our chances of successfully coming back via the cleric Deathpact spell.  Awhile back there was heavy debate in the chanter and cleric forums that high charisma increased the odds that someone would bounce back after death from the Deathpact spell if they had higher CHA.  So this may end up being an important stat at the very end game.<br>
<br>
Anyhow my point is while AC is indeed importantant if your faced with an armor choice where you could shave a few AC for some superb stats I would take the stats 9 times out of 10.  Couple that with the fact that most Velious and Luclin Armors come with stats anyhow it really become less of a sacrifice in the end.  Kunark armor was on the whole one of the silliest designs for armor I ever thought of, barring the BP legs and Helm (due to its effect). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubizomb.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bizomb</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 822<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/22/02 8:09:13 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14987.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: AC vs Stats revisited...not an equipment check :)</span><hr size=1> Ac is king, but don't sacrifice all else for it. <br>
